The paper proposes a method for visualizing and understanding the decision-making process of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves attention mechanisms, which are also commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also includes experiments on three different datasets, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
